[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care-coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: enrollment and consent (with cross-system data-access scope), longitudinal-store initialization, channel entry with disclosure, input safety screening, identity-and-cross-system-context loading with workflow-state inspection, conversation handling with cross-system-grounded responses, output safety screening with scope and clinical-interpretation discipline, task-execution with audit trail, warm-handoff routing to the care manager when applicable, and audit logging with care-coordination-specific retention. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (cross-system context-assembly with consent-gated access scope, workflow-state tracking as a stateful primitive, care-manager partnership infrastructure, multi-party conversation with consent-gated access scope, and care-transitions-window discipline).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ENROLLMENT + CROSS-SYSTEM CONSENT ─────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient enrolls via institution app, payer            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    benefits portal, or care-management platform]         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Documented consent specific to care-coordination    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      assistant interaction                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cross-system data-access scope: which providers,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      which data classes (clinical, claims, pharmacy,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      social-services), which time horizon                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Family-caregiver involvement: who, what scope,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      consent posture, capacity considerations            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team information-sharing posture               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Crisis-resource information surfaced                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Privacy posture explained in plain language         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (including 42 CFR Part 2 implications where         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      substance-use treatment data is in scope, and       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      state-specific mental-health-record protections     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      where mental-health data is in scope)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: signed consent record; enrollment             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    confirmation; initialization of longitudinal store]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── LONGITUDINAL STORE INITIALIZATION ─────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient-bot longitudinal store]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active conditions and care-coordination program     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      enrollment                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Authorized provider list (the providers covered by  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the patient's consented data-access scope)          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-management-team assignment (named primary      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      care manager, named backup, escalation chain)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Family-caregiver designation and consent posture    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stated patient preferences (preferred name,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      language, reading level, channel preferences,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      engagement-intensity preference, topics off-limits, │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      best times to reach)                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conversation history (initially empty)              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Workflow-state pointer                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-transition-state flags                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Consent posture (sharing scope, retention scope,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      family-caregiver scope)                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: longitudinal store ready for care-            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    coordination conversations]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CHANNEL ENTRY WITH DISCLOSURE ─────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient-initiated entry]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - In-app chat (most common for engaged patients)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - SMS (with TCPA-compliant consent for             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      message volume)                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Web chat                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Voice channel (with accessibility and disclosure    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      considerations, particularly for older-adult        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      cohorts)                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Bot-initiated entry, with care]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Workflow-state-triggered nudges (referral           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      overdue, prior-auth response received, post-        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      discharge follow-up due, gap-in-care reminder)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-transition-event-triggered outreach            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (post-discharge first-contact within 48-72          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      hours, post-procedure check-in, post-ER visit       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      follow-up)                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager-requested between-touch check-ins      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot-initiation respects engagement-intensity        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      preference, quiet hours, and channel preferences    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Multi-party authentication]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient identity verified                           │
