[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      no simulated friendship, no first-person            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      emotional claims)                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-party disclosure compliance (response only    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      contains content the present party is consented     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      to receive)                                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Crisis-pathway-honor check                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: response cleared for delivery, replaced       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    with safer template, or regenerated with corrections] │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── TASK EXECUTION + WORKFLOW STATE UPDATE ────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient-confirmed task execution]                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient confirms task before bot acts (for          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tasks with state-changing implications)             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Task executed via the appropriate source-system     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tool (scheduling system, portal-message API,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      referral platform, payer platform, pharmacy         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      interface, transportation interface, social-        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      services platform)                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Task result returned to the patient                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Workflow-state store updated with the task          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      execution and the resulting state transition        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Asynchronous workflow tracking]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tasks that resolve asynchronously (referral         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      scheduled later, prior-auth response later,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pharmacy refill processed later) are tracked in     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the workflow-state store                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Source-system events trigger workflow-state         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      transitions                                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot surfaces transitions to the patient and         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      care manager as appropriate                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: task executed, workflow-state-store updated,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    audit record written]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── WARM HANDOFF + ESCALATION ROUTING ─────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Warm-handoff triggers]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Out-of-scope clinical question                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient explicitly requests human                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Deteriorating-symptom report                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Sensitive disclosure pattern detected               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot confidence below threshold                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mandatory-reporting disclosure detected             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient pattern indicates worsening trajectory      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-transition risk signal                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager-requested handoff                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Handoff targets]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active medical emergency: 911 with stay-on-the-     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      line guidance                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mental-health crisis: route to recipe 11.8          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      patterns and 988                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Acute clinical concern: care-manager warm           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      handoff (or PCP office during business hours,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      after-hours nurse line otherwise)                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Routine care-manager handoff: warm handoff to       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      assigned care manager                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team handoff: PCP office, specialist           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      office, or pharmacy via the appropriate channel     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mandatory-reporting routing                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Social-services-urgent-need routing                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Warm-handoff payload]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent conversation transcript                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cross-system context summary                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Open workflow items                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Trigger reason and confidence                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient's preferred contact method                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient's stated preferences                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Bridge-and-stay pattern]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot bridges to care manager within the platform     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot stays present until care manager has joined     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient does not start over                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: handoff event with structured payload,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    conversation continuity preserved]                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND POST-MARKET SURVEILLANCE ──────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances (per party)                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated bot responses                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cross-system context loaded with citations          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Workflow-state store version                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active care-coordination-content corpus version     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Care-coordination-specific retention discipline]      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to longest of HIPAA's six-year      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, state-specific medical-record retention    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      rules, 42 CFR Part 2 retention for substance-use    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      treatment data where applicable, payer contractual  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      requirements (often longer than state minimums      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      for value-based-care contracts), and any            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      litigation-hold obligations                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Sensitive-disclosure surface separately governed    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      with restricted access                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Attrition rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager-leverage ratio                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Workflow-completion rate (referrals scheduled,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      prior-auths approved, follow-ups completed,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      gaps-in-care closed)                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Warm-handoff completion rate                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-to-task-execution                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      flags, payer, market)                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome-correlation pipeline]                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-window correlation against readmission        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      rate, ED utilization, total cost of care, gaps-     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      in-care closure, patient-experience scores,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      mortality (with appropriate caution about           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      attribution)                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort outcome tracking                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - CMS-quality-measure-alignment reporting             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-quality review]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      escalations, handoffs, and low-confidence           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      interactions                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (care managers, clinicians) tag           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      failure modes (out-of-scope, citation-gap,          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      workflow-state-error, missed-escalation, false-     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      escalation, multi-party-disclosure-violation,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tone-failure, equity-disparity)                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-coordination-content-corpus-revision proposals]  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care-coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-system context-assembly with consent-gated access scope as architectural primitive.** The bot operates across multiple data sources, each with its own consent posture, access scope, rate limits, and data quality. The cross-system retrieval pipeline holds the consent-and-access logic.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Workflow-state tracking as a stateful primitive.** The workflow-state store is a first-class entity with its own data model, its own update events from source systems, and its own tools for inspection. The bot reads the store; the workflow-state engine maintains it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-manager partnership infrastructure with capacity sizing.** The care-manager workforce is sized to the patient population and the expected handoff volume. The care-manager-side tooling shows the bot's open items, escalations, and recent conversations (with consent) so the care manager can manage their panel effectively.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-party conversation discipline with consent-gated access scope.** Per-party authentication, per-party access scope, per-party disclosure compliance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-transitions-window discipline.** Transition events trigger transition-specific cadence, task lists, and escalation thresholds reviewed by clinical leadership.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Social-determinants integration with privacy posture.** Social-services data has different privacy considerations than clinical data; the integration is reviewed by legal counsel.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Equity monitoring with launch-gate discipline.** Per-cohort engagement, attrition, workflow-completion, gaps-in-care closure, readmission, and care-manager-leverage metrics with launch-gate thresholds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every cross-system data point cited with source-of-record and retrieval timestamp. Workflow-state assertions grounded in the workflow-state store. Plain-language explanations grounded in clinician-stated source content.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology with care-pathway resilience.** When a source system is unreachable, the bot is honest about the gap, surfaces alternative pathways, and routes to the care manager. Per-source failover is documented and exercised quarterly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
